de.payleven.inappsdk.listeners

Interface SetPaymentInstrumentsOrderListener


  • public interface SetPaymentInstrumentsOrderListener
    Listener for setting the order of payment instruments In case of failure, a throwable containing the reason will be give as parameter

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onPaymentInstrumentsSetFailed(Throwable throwable)
      Called when the payment instrument order setting failed

    • Method Detail

      • onPaymentInstrumentsSetSuccessfully

        void onPaymentInstrumentsSetSuccessfully(int numberOfPaymentInstrumentsReordered)
        Called when the order of payment instruments finished successfully
        Parameters:
        numberOfPaymentInstrumentsReordered - number of payment instruments that were reordered

      • onPaymentInstrumentsSetFailed

        void onPaymentInstrumentsSetFailed(Throwable throwable)
        Called when the payment instrument order setting failed
        Parameters:
        throwable - the error that caused the order setting failure For more details on the reason of the failure check for the instance of the Throwable. If the Throwable is a CallbackError the error code and the message encapsulated can give more insight.

        Possible instances are:

        NetworkError - in case the error was caused by a network error

        MissingPaymentInstrumentsError if the PaymentInstrument parameter of the request was null

        InvalidUserTokenError if the request was called with an invalid user token
